value.name: low freq deactivation scale
value.tooltip: 0 is default (1). LESS than 1 deactivates less aggressively. GREATER than 1 is more agressive.

value.name: high freq deactivation scale
value.tooltip: 0 is default (1). LESS than 1 deactivates less aggressively. GREATER than 1 is more agressive.

value.name: marker name
value.tooltip: you don't need this if you're just generating effects. If empty it defaults to the up of the object

value.name: alignment marker name
value.tooltip: you don't need this if you're just generating effects. If empty it defaults to "marker name"

value.name: hookes law e
value.tooltip: 0 if you don't want this to behave like spring. 1 is a good starting point if you do.

value.name: linear dead radius
value.tooltip: radius from linear motion origin in which acceleration is dead.

value.name: alignment hookes law e
value.tooltip: 0 if you don't want this to behave like spring. 1 is a good starting point if you do.

bit.name: is rigid
bit.tooltip: this constraint makes the edge rigid until it is loosened by damage

bit.name: disable effects
bit.tooltip: this constraint will not generate impact effects

value.name: friction
value.tooltip: 0 is the default (takes what it was set in max) anything else overrides that value

value.name: node a material
value.tooltip: if you don't fill this out we will pluck the material from the first primitive, of the first rigid body attached to node a

value.name: node b material
value.tooltip: if you don't fill this out we will pluck the material from the first primitive, of the first rigid body attached to node b, if node b is none we use whatever material a has

bit.name: disable effects
bit.tooltip: this rigid body will not generate impact effects unless it hits another dynamic rigid body that does

bit.name: does not interact w/environment
bit.tooltip: set this flag if this rigid bodies won't touch the environment, this allows us to open up some optimizations

bit.name: best early mover body
bit.tooltip: if you have either of the early mover flags set in the object definitoin this body will be choosen as the one to make every thing local to, otherwise I pick :-)

bit.name: has no phantom power version
bit.tooltip: don't check this flag without talking to eamon

value.name: linear damping
value.tooltip: this goes from 0-10 (10 is really, really high)

value.name: angular damping
value.tooltip: this goes from 0-10 (10 is really, really high)

value.name: bounding sphere pad
value.tooltip: the bounding sphere for this rigid body will be outset by this much

bit.name: does not collide with fixed bodies
